{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Troubleshooting - Wisp Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Troubleshooting</h1>

<p>Common issues and solutions.</p>

<h2>Common Errors</h2>

<h3>"variable not found: X"</h3>
<p>Variable X is not in the data map.</p>
<pre><code>{# Check data map #}
data := map[string]interface{}{
    "name": "Alice",  {# This exists #}
    {# "email" missing #}
}

{# Use default to debug #}
{%.email | default "NOT_FOUND"}</code></pre>

<h3>"template not found: X"</h3>
<p>Template file does not exist or not registered.</p>
<pre><code>{# Register template manually #}
e.RegisterTemplate("header", "&lt;header&gt;Header&lt;/header&gt;")

{# Or ensure file exists in template directory #}</code></pre>

<h3>"parse errors"</h3>
<p>Template syntax is invalid.</p>
<pre><code>{# Common mistakes #}
{% if .show %}     {# Missing {% end %} #}
{%.name }}       {# Extra } #}

{# Validate before rendering #}
e.Validate(template)</code></pre>

<h3>Output shows escaped HTML</h3>
<p>Auto-escaping is on by default.</p>
<pre><code>{# Use raw for trusted content #}
{%.trusted_html | raw}

{# Or disable auto-escaping for non-HTML #}
e.SetAutoEscape(false)</code></pre>

<h2>Rendering Issues</h2>

<h3>Variables not accessible in include/render</h3>
<pre><code>{# include: shares parent scope - works #}
{% assign .name = "Alice" %}
{% include "partials/greeting" %}

{# render: isolated scope - parent vars not available #}
{% assign .name = "Alice" %}
{% render "widget" .data %}{# Cannot access .name #}</code></pre>

<h3>Blocks not overriding</h3>
<pre><code>{# Ensure extends is FIRST #}
{% extends "layouts/base" %}

{% block content %}
    This should work
{% end %}</code></pre>

<h2>Debugging Tips</h2>

<h3>Print Variables</h3>
<pre><code>{# Use json filter to see data #}
{%. | json %}
{%.user | json }

{# Use default to check #}
{%.name | default "NOT_SET"}</code></pre>

<h3>Validate Templates</h3>
<pre><code>func validateTemplate(template string) error {
    e := engine.New()
    return e.Validate(template)
}</code></pre>

<h2>FAQ</h2>

<h3>How do I pass data to included templates?</h3>
<pre><code>{# Parent variables are accessible in include #}
{% assign .title = "Home" %}
{% include "partials/header" %}

{# Or pass additional data #}
{% include "partials/card" .card_data %}</code></pre>

<h3>Why isn't my custom filter working?</h3>
<pre><code>{# Register filter #}
e.RegisterFilter("myfilter", func(input interface{}) string {
    return strings.ToUpper(toString(input))
})

{# Use without parens #}
{%.name | myfilter}</code></pre>

<h3>How do I render JSON?</h3>
<pre><code>{# Disable auto-escaping for JSON #}
e.SetAutoEscape(false)

{# Use json filter #}
{%.data | json}</code></pre>

